#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:1986
msgid ""
"Evaluates on a cell-by-cell basis the frequency (number of times) the "
"values of an input stack of rasters are less than the value of a value "
"raster. The output raster extent and resolution is defined by the input "
"raster layer and is always of ``Int32`` type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:1999
msgid ""
"For each cell in the output raster, the value represents the number of "
"times that the corresponding cells in the list of rasters are less than "
"the value raster. ``NoData`` cells (grey) are taken into account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2003
msgid ":ref:`qgisequaltofrequency`, :ref:`qgisgreaterthanfrequency`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2014
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:lessthanfrequency``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2024
msgid "Lowest position in raster stack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2026
msgid ""
"Evaluates on a cell-by-cell basis the position of the raster with the "
"lowest value in a stack of rasters. Position counts start with 1 and "
"range to the total number of input rasters. The order of the input "
"rasters is relevant for the algorithm. If multiple rasters feature the "
"lowest value, the first raster will be used for the position value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2043
msgid ":ref:`qgishighestpositioninrasterstack`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2054
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:lowestpositioninrasterstack``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2064
msgid "Raster boolean AND"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2065
msgid ""
"Calculates the boolean ``AND`` for a set of input rasters. If all of the "
"input rasters have a non-zero value for a pixel, that pixel will be set "
"to ``1`` in the output raster. If any of the input rasters have ``0`` "
"values for the pixel it will be set to ``0`` in the output raster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2071
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2241
msgid ""
"The reference layer parameter specifies an existing raster layer to use "
"as a reference when creating the output raster. The output raster will "
"have the same extent, CRS, and pixel dimensions as this layer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2076
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasteranalysis.rst:2246
msgid ""
"By default, a NoData pixel in ANY of the input layers will result in a "
"NoData pixel in the output raster. If the :guilabel:`Treat NoData values "
"as false` option is checked, then NoData inputs will be treated the same "
"as a ``0`` input value."
