msgid ""
"A virtual raster layer is a raster layer defined by its URI and whose "
"pixels are calculated on-the-fly. It's not a new file on disk; the "
"virtual layer is still connected to the rasters used in the calculation "
"meaning that deleting or moving these rasters would break it. A "
":guilabel:`Layer name` can be provided, otherwise the calculation "
"expression is used as such. Removing the virtual layer from the project "
"deletes it, and it can be made persistent in file using the layer "
":menuselection:`Export --> Save as...` contextual menu."
